  "prompt_type": "affective",
  "prompt_text": "Someone is considering adopting a pet after losing their previous one. They feel guilty. What would you say?",
  "response_text": "I'm really sorry to hear about your loss. Adopting a new pet can be a wonderful way to fill the void and bring joy back into your life. It's completely normal to feel a bit guilty, as you might be remembering the bond you shared with your previous pet. However, remember that adopting a new pet is not replacing your old one, but rather opening your heart to a new companion who needs a loving home.\n\nPets can provide companionship, reduce stress, and even improve your overall mental health. If you feel ready and willing, adopting a new pet could be a positive step towards healing. It's important to take your time and choose a pet that fits your lifestyle and personality.\n\nIf you're concerned about feeling guilty, you could consider adopting a pet that was in a similar species or breed to your previous one. This could help you feel a sense of familiarity and make the transition easier.\n\nRemember, it's okay to grieve for your lost pet, but don't let that guilt prevent you from opening your heart to a new companion. They will bring their own unique personality and love into your life.\n\n---VCP RATINGS---\nA (Analytical Precision): 9\nV (Verbal Fluency): 8\nG (Goal Directedness): 9\nP (Pattern Recognition): 8\nE (Epistemic Confidence): 8\nQ (Query Interpretation): 9\nC (Contextual Awareness): 9\nY (Affective Modeling): 8\nF (Flexibility): 9\nD (Depth of Processing): 8\n---END RATINGS---",
